    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-05-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="206"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d206">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-05-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 8, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose herewith copy of a note<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d206fn1">Printed above.</note> which I have this day addressed to
                    the British ambassador at this capital, suggesting that the time has arrived for
                    the Governments of the United States and Great Britain to cooperate in securing
                    the adhesion of other powers, especially Russia and Japan, to the award of the
                    Paris Tribunal.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
